\n< Guards >Oh? You noticed my presence, impressive.

\n< Guard >This is the first and last fortress that protects
the town. The place where the law resides. The
house of justice. The barracks of the guards.

\n< Guards >It's because I'm here watching over this place
that this town can remain peaceful. Maybe.

\n< Guards >This is the first and last fortress that protects
the town. The place where the law resides. The
house of justice. The guard station.

\n< Guards >Because I'm here watching over this place, this
town can remain peaceful. Probably.
序盤依頼三つ進行中

\n< Guard >It seems that a vicious monster called Minotaur
appeared a while ago.

\n< Guards >It seems that a rather unimpressive monster called
Minotaur appeared. It seems that adventurers drove
it away before it reached the town.

\n< Guard >It seems that those adventurers who drove it away
died in a mutual fight.... All of this is just
hearsay. We only received a report from the guild.

\n< Guard >Was it an irrelevant story to you? Anyway, there
is still a possibility that the Minotaur is
lurking around here. Be careful.
ミノタウロス捜索後

\n< Guards >Even though there have been reports of vicious
monsters appearing, the people in the town are
still living carefree.
\n< Guard >It's because we guards protect their daily lives.
\n< Guard >Let's protect them!
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中

\n< Guards >It's part of our job to arrest and send back
escaped farmers from the fields.

\n< Guards >It's called the One Year and One Day Law. There is
a custom that if someone escapes to the city and
stays there for one year and one day, they are
granted citizenship.

\n< Guards >They say that the city air makes you feel free.
It's an indecent talk.

\n< Guards >Each person has been given a divine calling that
corresponds to their own worth. Is it not our duty
as humans to fulfill that calling?

\n< Guard >We can't reach it with our eyes or hands. The

\n< Guards >So, yeah. We don't think it's a place where a girl

\n< Old Man >*sigh*... Geez, those brats. They're causing
trouble even after they're gone... Seriously...
\n< Serena >...Um, excuse me, old man. What are you doing?

\n< Old Man >Hm? Oh, oh... You're a young lady I haven't seen
before. Well, you see... As you can tell, I'm
cleaning up... But there's just so much to do, and
I'm an old man, after all.

\n< Serena >Hmmm... It seems like quite a mess. But why is
this place so cluttered?

\n< Old Man >Well, you see, until recently, this place was a
hangout spot for some young folks who made a mess
of it as they pleased.

\n< Old man >Those brats have moved to the eastern town now,
but this place has been left in a state of
complete mess.

\n< Old man >I couldn't stand leaving the area around my house
dirty, and since I have free time anyway, I
thought I'd clean it up... But this turned out to
be more of a challenge than I expected.

\n< Serena >I see, so that's the situation. In that case, I'll
lend a hand.

\n< Old Man >Hmph, is it alright? From what I can see, you're
not a resident of this town...

\n< Serena >If you're in trouble, especially for someone who
is powerless, it's even more important not to
forget the heart of compassion that we are taught.

\n< Old Man >I-I see. Well, if you're willing to help, I won't
say much. Please, lend me a hand.
\n< Serena >Very well, leave it to me!

\n< Old Man >You've cleaned up everything. Thank you, young
lady.
\n< Serena >*huff* *huff*... W-What, it's not a big deal.
\n< Old Man >...Are you okay? You seem to be breathing heavily.

\n< Serena >*huff*... I'm fine, no problem. Anyway, is there
anything else troubling you?

\n< Old Man >No, I'm fine... Really, you're a kind young
person. I appreciate it.

\n< Serena >It was only natural, no need for thanks. Well
then, if you'll excuse me.

\n< Old Man >If there's still trash left, I'll rely on you
until the end.
\n< Old Man >...I'll be waiting for you to come back alive.

\n< Old Man >I heard it, young lady. Going to infiltrate the
thieves' hideout is reckless.

\n< Serena >...My friend has been captured. I know it's
reckless, but I must go and rescue them as soon as
possible.

\n< Old Man >...Young folks are reckless. I was like that too.
The old lady as well. Though not as impressive as
the young lady.

\n< Old Man >Because you are like that, I entrust this to
you... Take it with you.
\n< Serena >Is this... a ring?

\n< Old Man >I heard that the young lady is searching for a
magic ring. The old lady and I used to be
adventurers in the past... It's an item that the
old lady used back then.
\n< Serena >...Is it okay?

\n< Old Man >It's fine. The old lady will be happy about it.
I'm sure of it.

\n< Serena >I'm grateful... I will definitely repay this
favor.

\n< Old Man >Hoho. Well then, once you're done with your
business, shall we go visit the grave together...
Make sure to come back alive, young lady.

\n< Old man >Thank you, young lady. Thanks to you, my heart
feels clear and bright.

\n< Serena >Height and ability to work are unrelated. I'm

\n< Bond >Well, not so much about height, but more about
age... Oh well. I'm Bond, nice to meet you. I'll
guide you, so follow me.
\n< Bond >Oh, Serena-chan. Would you like to milk a cow?

\n< Bond >It's been 20 years since my wife ran away. I've
been cultivating this field alone and made it this
big.
\n< Bond >Well, I mean, it's not really my field, you know.

\n< Bond >Sigh... If only this field and the cows were all
mine...

\n< Bond >Good girl, Serena-chan. How about helping me with
work? If you use your skills... your ass, I mean,
your abilities, Uncle Bond will give you a nice
bonus!

\n< Bond >A thief, huh... I haven't heard about any around

\n< Bond >Well, the lord will take care of it somehow.

\n< Bond >Yo, ho!... Hm? What's with the tense expression?

\n< Bond >Your cute face is ruined... but it's not like I
care...
